name: Devin Brugman
description:
Devin Brugman is an American model and social media celebrity with more than 1M followers in Instagram.

Update: Retrained from scratch for 200 steps, using a dataset of 18 images and with these settings. Devin's was my 2nd TI here at CivitAI, if I recall correctly, and it was about time to update it. She's one of my favorite models and I've always wanted to make her justice with a good embedding. In fact, Devin was the fist subject I ever tried to make an embedding of, back in January this year... The attempt was such a disaster that I stopped trying for about a month. If you want to have a good laugh, here are the training images the AI generated while learning Dev's physique. The best part is I let it run up until step 4000. I probably was expecting it to improve at some point :_D. (By the way, the attempt was so bad for 2 main reasons: first, because I used Protogen as the training model instead of standard SD, and second because I used a 512x768 format. Rookie mistakes. ^^)

Appreciate my work? My TIs are free, but you can always buy me a coffee. :)

Curious about my work process? I have summarized it here.

Building a good prompt with my TIs

You're obviously free to experiment, but bear in mind that my TIs are trained with a more or less fixed phrasing, that normally starts with:

"photo of EMBEDDING_NAME, a woman"

So I recommend always starting your prompt like that and then building the rest of the prompt from there. For instance, "photo of beautiful (devjugsman:0.99), a woman as a movie star, sweater off-shoulders, trousers, at a movie premiere gala, dark moody ambience (masterpiece:1.2) (photorealistic:1.2) (bokeh) (best quality) (detailed skin:1.2) (intricate details) (nighttime) (8k) (HDR) (cinematic lighting) (sharp focus), (looking at the camera:1.1), (closeup portrait:1.1)"
